# Fluff Date: 2026-02-28 17:47:08
overview:<p>The Nova Cat is a 70-ton Clan heavy OmniMech introduced in 3059, commissioned by Khan Severen Leroux of Clan Nova Cat following the Clan's devastating defeat at the Battle of Tukayyid. Designed to rebuild both the touman's fighting strength and the Clan's shattered morale, the Nova Cat was christened after the Clan's spiritual namesake, imbuing it with deep symbolic significance for its warriors. The design draws heavy inspiration from Clan Jade Falcon's Night Gyr, trading five tons of mass for equivalent pod capacity through efficient use of an Endo Steel chassis and XL engine.</p><p>First produced at Barcella Alpha in Clan space, production expanded almost immediately to the Irece Alpha facility in the Inner Sphere. This dual-site manufacturing proved critical when Clan Nova Cat was abjured by the other Clans, ensuring uninterrupted production. The design's combination of heavy armor, generous pod space, and straightforward maintenance requirements made it popular well beyond its parent Clan, spreading rapidly to numerous other Clan and Inner Sphere factions over the following decades.</p>

capabilities:<p>Long regarded as a pocket assault OmniMech, the Nova Cat sacrifices speed for firepower and protection. Its Consolidated Fusion 280 XL engine propels the seventy-ton chassis at a modest 43 kph cruising speed and 65 kph maximum, slower than most Clan heavies but sufficient for fire support and direct engagement roles. With over half its tonnage dedicated to weapons, ammunition, and equipment, the 38 tons of available pod space rivals many assault OmniMechs, giving technicians extraordinary flexibility in tailoring loadouts to mission requirements.</p><p>The Mynx Type Heavy Endo Steel frame supports 13.5 tons of Alpha Compound Plate armor, approaching the maximum protection possible for this weight class. Combined with a Clan XL engine that remains operational even after side torso loss, the Nova Cat is exceptionally difficult to destroy. Straightforward internal construction using common Clan components ensures rapid field repairs and reconfigurations, a significant logistical advantage for units operating far from supply lines.</p><p>The Primary configuration exemplifies the design's philosophy with two ER PPCs and three ER Large Lasers, creating a withering long-range energy barrage. Twenty-five double heat sinks struggle to dissipate a full alpha strike, but the all-energy loadout allows extended independent operations without ammunition concerns, and disciplined fire grouping keeps the 'Mech combat-effective indefinitely.</p>

deployment:<p>The B configuration departs dramatically from the energy-focused philosophy of the Primary and A variants, transforming the Nova Cat into a dedicated missile boat. Six LRM-15 launchers deliver devastating indirect fire barrages, while a pair of ER Medium Lasers provide close-range self-defense. Five additional double heat sinks handle the relatively modest thermal load, allowing sustained volleys. The platform's resemblance to the Night Gyr D configuration is no coincidence, as Nova Cat engineers drew directly from Jade Falcon design philosophy when developing this variant. The combination of the Nova Cat's heavy armor with massed missile fire makes this configuration a formidable garrison and fire support asset.</p>

history:<p>The Nova Cat's origins are inseparable from the crisis that gripped Clan Nova Cat after Tukayyid. The Clan's defeat in 3052 shook its warriors to the core, and Khan Severen Leroux's decision to commission a new OmniMech was as much about restoring spiritual confidence as rebuilding military capability. Production began at Barcella Alpha, the Nova Cat capital world, and expanded to the Irece Alpha plant in early 3059 as the Clan began establishing its presence in the Inner Sphere.</p><p>The Nova Cat first saw significant combat during Operation Bulldog in 3059, when Clan Nova Cat's warriors turned their new OmniMech against Clan Smoke Jaguar. When the 357th Assault Cluster took Dyev from the Draconis Combine, the versatility of several Nova Cats proved decisive, with configurations mounting heavy autocannons and cluster munitions devastating militia vehicles and infantry formations. The sight of the towering twelve-meter 'Mech stalking through battlefield smoke became a potent psychological weapon against defending forces.</p><p>The Clan's Abjuration following their alliance with the Second Star League scattered Nova Cats across multiple factions' arsenals. Several units were seized by Clan Smoke Jaguar forces when they captured a malfunctioning Nova Cat DropShip during the chaos surrounding the Clan's dissolution. Sources in the Periphery persistently reported sightings of machines resembling the Nova Cat, suggesting that salvaged or captured examples may have entered the arsenals of Clans that accepted Smoke Jaguar refugees. The design also spread through more conventional channels, with Clan Diamond Shark's acquisition of the Barcella Alpha facility during the Civil War era enabling broader commercial distribution.</p><p>The Jihad proved devastating for Nova Cat production. The Irece Alpha plant was destroyed in 3071 during the Word of Blake's assault on the Draconis Combine, and individual Nova Cats were documented fighting desperate engagements against Blakist forces on worlds like Luthien and Caph. Despite the death of Clan Nova Cat as a political entity, the Tiburon Khanate maintained the Irece factory after it was rebuilt in the 3090s, meeting continued demand that proved both expected and surprising. Salvaged Nova Cats became a fixture in the Rasalhague Dominion, where native warriors of the former Free Rasalhague Republic put them to effective use despite being shunned by their Ghost Bear overlords.</p><p>By the ilClan era, the Nova Cat OmniMech had long outlived its parent Clan. Production continued at Irece under Draconis Combine control, while the Barcella facility's ownership passed through multiple Clan hands. Among the warriors of the Clan Protectorate, Nova Cat OmniMechs remain highly prized assets that frequently change hands through Trials of Possession, a fitting legacy for a design born from one Clan's determination to endure.</p>

